title.narrative: Health systems provide improved quality of care from pregnancy to adolescence for MNCH and HIV.

description.narrative: UNICEF and other partners support the Government to equip health facilities and improve the quality of services, including ensuring timely referrals and recovery from a partial interruption of services during COVID-19 response. With direct UNICEF support, 93 health facilities received equipment for maternal, newborn and childcare. UNICEF also supported improved newborn care in 93 health facilities and intrapartum care in 42 facilities, in partnership with professional associations. UNICEF supported to strengthen cold chain systems and made efforts to improve quality of care for persons living with HIV, including adolescents. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/08/2020
